HEADWORD: Ophiuroidea
<hw>O`phi*u*roi"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'o`fis</grk> serpent + <grk>'oyra`</grk> tail +
<grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A class of
star-shaped echinoderms having a disklike body, with slender,
articulated arms, which are not grooved beneath and are often very
fragile; -- called also <altname>Ophiuroida</altname> and
<altname>Ophiuridea</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Brittle
star</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

